      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elastic-plastic constitutive model with frictional contact is appropriate for quasi-static compression-bending of metallic implant constructs; justification documented.",
      "rationale": "The von Mises elastic-plastic model with isotropic hardening and Coulomb friction contact (μ=0.3) is consistent with published literature for titanium alloy spinal implant simulation under quasi-static loading. Strain-rate effects are negligible at the prescribed 5 mm/min test rate. Model form is appropriate for the COU. Achieved level equals required level; criterion met."
