      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA model inputs (geometry, material properties, boundary conditions) are demonstrably equivalent to the physical test configuration within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Fixture geometry in the FEA model was constructed from engineering drawings of the F1717 test fixtures and verified against CMM scans of the actual fixtures. Boundary conditions replicate the pin-pin loading articulation. Material properties match coupon measurements. Equivalency is documented in the model validation report. Achieved level equals required level; criterion met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
