      "acceptanceCriteria": "Selected QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) are directly linked to the clinical decision criteria and the ASTM F1717 regulatory acceptance standard.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield force are the primary mechanical endpoints specified in ASTM F1717 and cited in FDA guidance for pedicle screw 510(k) submissions. Force at 40 mm displacement captures post-yield behavior relevant to fatigue failure initiation. All three QoIs are directly traceable to the device risk model. Achieved level equals required level; criterion met."
