      "rationale": "The validation activity directly replicates the COU: the same screw design, rod diameter, pedicle screw spacing, and loading protocol are used in both the FEA model and the bench test. The two-laboratory design strengthens external validity. The single loading condition gap (Test conditions factor) is bounded by the conservative acceptance thresholds. Overall, the validation activities are sufficiently relevant to support a Medium assurance level determination. Achieved level equals required level; criterion met."
